#;   374. PicassoChipsetPkg\UsbLegacyControl\UsbLegacyControl.c
#;   375. PicassoChipsetPkg\UsbLegacyControl\UsbLegacyControl.h
#; 
#; Tag#: 05.38.09.0023
#; Issue#: IB18160199
#; Severity: Minor
#; Category: Setup Utility
#; Symptom: Can't load correct default value under AMD CBS/PBS after change default value by H2OEZE.
#; RootCause: H2O Setup utility will load constant default value for AMD CBS/PBS form by PI industry function but not variable default.
#; Description: H2OEZE modify Setup default value by adjust variable default.
#;              Since AMD CBS/PBS will not load default by what variable defined.
#;              It can not load to specific value after adjust.  
#; Solution: Adjust Setup load default function to load variable first.
#;           The PI load default function will only trigger when load variable default failed. 
#; SolutionDependency: None.
#; Reviewer: IB18160000

#; Severity: Minor
#; Category: Setup Utility
#; Symptom: Adjust AMD PBS form variable default value by VFR file, but load default the value load to origin default value.
#; RootCause: AMD PI will directly load default by industry function for AMD PBS form.

#; Issue#: IB18160163
#; Severity: Minor
#; Category: Others
#; Symptom: 16M BIOS Build failed
#; RootCause: PSP bios direct didn't dynamic fit to 16M BIOS flash map

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0022
#; Issue#: IB18160154
#; Severity: Serious
#; Category: Security
#; Symptom: (Security)
#; RootCause: (Security)
#; Description: (ITS: 0109335) Cleartext storage of system password could lead to possible information disclosure (CVE-2023-31041)
#;              1. When set PcdSecureSysPasswordSupported to TRUE, if admin variable already exists and user changes
#;              the supervisor password by system password protocol SetPassword() without calling DisablePassword()
#;              first, the password cannot modify.
#;              2. If the admin variable already exists, when changing supervisor password by SysPasswordProtocol->SetPassword(),
#;              the admin variable will update. However, the TimeStamp of the variable will be filled with 0 according to
#;              the flow of UpdateVariable(). It will cause the next time user cannot modify the password and return
#;              EFI_WRITE_PROTECTED when update admin variable since we will check whether TimeStamp is filled with 0xFF to
#;              confirm whether it is an Insyde secure variable in IsExistingInsydeSecureVariable(). Therefore, if update variable
#;              is admin variable, fill TimeStamp with 0xFF.
#; Solution: (Security)  IB19130134 (Kernel issue fixed patch)
#; SolutionDependency: IB19130134 fixes side effect of IB19130117 (adopted at 05.60.19/05.53.19/05.45.19/05.37.19/05.28.19).
#; Reviewer: IB18160000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Modified:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\BIOS\BILBY.fd
#;   2. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\Variable\VariableRuntimeDxe\Variable.c

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0022
#; Issue#: IB18160149
#; Severity: Serious
#; Category: Security
#; Symptom: (Security)
#; RootCause: (Security)
#; Description: (ITS: 0111402) Arbitrary calls to SetVariable with unsanitized arguments in SMI handler. In VatsWrite(), SetVariable called from SMM is allowed to overwrite _locked_ variables. (CVE-2023-39284)
#;              (ITS: 0112222) H2O0900: Add H2O_SMM_VARIABLE_LOCK_POLICY_PROTOCOL, VatsWrite() can use this protocol to enable variable in SMM.
#;              For detail, please refer to InsydeH2O UEFI Variable Technical Reference in P:\Engineering\Kernel\Core\H2O 5.0 folder.
#; Solution: (Security) IB02961598 (kernel issue fixed patch)
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB18160000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Added:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\InsydeModulePkg\Include\Protocol\H2OSmmVariableLockPolicy.h

#;             HddPassword option will appear in SCU.
#; RootCause: After adopting IB19130044, when if ATA_DEVICE_SERVER_PASSWORD command return device error, it will use SECURITY_PROTOCOL_INFORMATION to get

#;            it may judgment to be wrong for ATA Device Service Password Security supported status and lock status,
#;            this incorrect ATA Device Service Password Security supported status may cause this HddPassword option appear in SCU,
#;            and the incorrect lock status may cause the error returned when perform NVME EFI block IO read/write.

#;                  NvmExpressPei:       02.11.50.1206

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0019
#; Issue#: IB14860831
#; Severity: Fatal
#; Category: Security
#; Symptom: (Security)
#; RootCause: (Security)
#; Description: (CVE-2017-5715)(ITS98862)(IB02961084)(Kernel issue fixed patch)
#;              (CVE-2017-5715) Stuff RSB before RSM
#;              Return Stack Buffer (RSB) is used to predict the target of RET instructions. When the RSB underflows, some processors may fall back to
#;              using branch predictors. This might impact software using the retpoline mitigation strategy on those processors.
#;              Retpoline: a software construct for preventing branch-target-injection (Spectre). 
#; Solution:  This commit will add RSB stuffing logic before returning from SMM (the RSM instruction) to avoid interfering with non-SMM usage of the retpoline technique.
#;            (IB02961084)(Kernel issue fixed patch)
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB14860000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Added:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\UefiCpuPkg\
#;   2. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\UefiCpuPkg\Include\
#;   3. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\UefiCpuPkg\Include\StuffRsbNasm.inc
#;   4. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\
#;   5. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\
#;   6. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\SmmCpuFeaturesLib\
#;   7. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\SmmCpuFeaturesLib\Ia32\
#;   8. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\SmmCpuFeaturesLib\Ia32\SmiEntry.nasm
#;   9. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\SmmCpuFeaturesLib\Ia32\SmiException.nasm
#;   10. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\SmmCpuFeaturesLib\SmmCpuFeaturesLib.inf
#;   11. PicassoChipsetPkg\Override\UefiCpuPkg\Library\SmmCpuFeaturesLib\X64\

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0018
#; Issue#: IB14860819
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: HDD Password
#; Symptom: On AMD platform, when IOMMU enabled and storages(NVME & AHCI) are locked with HDD Password
#;          resume from S3 would observe BSOD.            
#; RootCause: Because AMD IOMMU design, when resume from S3, on AMD platform with IOMMU enabled, BIOS will need
#;            to re-map the host address for DMA access or all DMA commands will fail.
#;            This would lead to unlock fail and cause system BSOD.
#; Description:(CVE-2022-29278)(H2O-0401-2200)(ITS97902)(IB15850209)(kernel issue fixed patch)
#;             1.(Bug Fix).
#;             2.(This version of Seamless SATA will labeled as 02.09.23.0529.00)
#;                AhciBusDxe  : 02.09.23.0529.00
#;                IdeBusDxe   : 02.07.01.0105.00
#;                AhciBusPei  : 02.07.49.1205.00
#;                IdeBusPei   : 02.04.01.1228.00
#;                AtaLegacySmm: 02.07.25.0625.00
#;                StorageSecurityCommandDxe: 02.09.21.0520.00
#;             3.(This version of NVMe will labeled as 01.05.23.0529.00)
#;                 NvmExpressDxe:       01.05.23.0529
#;                 NvmExpressPei:       01.04.25.0618
#;                 NvmExpressLegacySmm: 01.05.11.0311
#; Solution: 1. Store DMA buffer addresses in lock box during POST. 
#;           2. When resume from S3, re-map them in PEI phase and then sync with 
#;              NVME & AHCI driver in SMM.     
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB14860000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Added:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\InsydeModulePkg\Package.fdf
#;   2. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\RemapIommuPei\
#;   3. BilbyBoardPkg\OverrideHeaderFile\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\RemapIommuPei\DmaMem.c

#; Category: HDD Password
#; Symptom: Calling SmmCommunication with "HDD_PASSWORD_ACPI_RESTORE_CALLBACK_NOTIFY_INSTANCE"
#;          function would observe EFI_Invalid parameter status returned.               
#; RootCause: Incorrect CommSize was assigned. Core code defines CommSize as the
#;            size of the whole buffer.                   
#; Description:(Kernel Bug Fix Patch) For S3 resume with HddPassword hang issue.                          
#; Solution: Use correct comsize for the function.

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0017
#; Issue#: IB14860794
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: HDD Password
#; Symptom: [ITS0079615]S3 long run stress would observe BSOD with NVMe device attached.             
#; RootCause: The issue is due to SMM RAM being use out.  When PcdH2OHddPasswordTcgOpalSupported set to FALSE
#;            and attach with NVMe that does not support ATA password, current code will
#;            allocate a zero size memory and then leave the function.  However, despite
#;            allocating a zero size memory, core code will still reserve 0x40 byte for 
#;            private data, this will eventually drain out SMM RAM.  
#; Description:(Kernel Bug Fix).
#; Solution: If the allocate size is 0, skip allocating and return.
#; SolutionDependency: IB15850279
#; Reviewer: IB14860000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Modified:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\BIOS\BILBY.fd
#;   2. BilbyBoardPkg\Override\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\Security\HddPassword\HddPassword.c
#; 
#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0017
#; Issue#: IB14860792
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: HDD Password
#; Symptom: 1. Attach a device pre-locked with TCG OPAL/Pyrite Admin password.
#;          2. Enter OS and then reboot to SCU will find a drive being shown unlocked. 
#; RootCause: TCG Opal/Pyrite comreset would check Admin1 password, but when
#;            fail to find one, it would still output an empty password & zero password length
#;            to the caller.  This empty password and  will kept using in RetrieveTcgPassword()
#;            when testing user1 password and cause EFI_Buffer_Too_Small error even though
#;            a User1 password was found.   
#; Description:(Kernel Bug Fix).
#; Solution: Check password length in RetrieveTcgPassword() to make sure empty password and length
#;           will not output to caller and continue being used. 
#; SolutionDependency: IB15850159
#; Reviewer: IB14860000 (Kernel 5.3 05.33.43)
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Modified:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\Override\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\Security\HddPassword\HddPassword.c
#; 
#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0017
#; Issue#: IB14860791
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: SATA
#; Symptom: After adopting IB15850145, it would take Hdd more than 2 second to resume from s3.             
#; RootCause: IB15850145 add code to check Hdd's security status by sending ATA identify command in s3 resume everytime.
#;            For Hdd, this command would fail and cause timeout until a ATA comreset.  Timeout
#;            would cause about 2 seconds.  
#; Description:(Kernel Bug Fix).
#; Solution: Remove the code that check Hdd's security status in s3 resume.  Modified
#;           code flow will do comreset first before checking Hdd's security status.
#; SolutionDependency: IB15850185 fix the side effect of IB15850145 (adopted on 05.33.44)
#; Reviewer: IB14860000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Modified:

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0015
#; Issue#: IB06070198
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: SATA
#; Symptom: On SATA drive that encrypted by Winmagic SecureDoc software, after input
#;          correct user ID and password, it would take more than a minute 
#;          to go from preboot login menu to Window OS.
#; RootCause: After IB15850101, BIOS will not install StorageSecurityCommand Protocol 
#;            on the device that found to be encrypted by 3rd party software. 
#;            However, After input correct user ID and password, Window OS will continue 
#;            send TCG related command by consuming StorageSecuritCommand protocol. Without the
#;            protocol, it looks like OS will pending a long time for trying to
#;            send commands.           
#; Description:1.(Bug Fix).
#;             2.(This version of Seamless SATA will labeled as 02.08.09.0304.00)
#;                AhciBusDxe  : 02.08.05.0129.00
#;                IdeBusDxe   : 02.07.01.0105.00
#;                AhciBusPei  : 02.07.49.1205.00
#;                IdeBusPei   : 02.04.01.1228.00
#;                AtaLegacySmm: 02.07.25.0625.00
#;                StorageSecurityCommandDxe: 02.08.09.0304.00
#; Solution: Enhance current policy that as long as the device support either ATA security
#;           or TCG storage security protocols, StorageSecurityCommand protocol instance
#;           will be installed on the device handle.  However, if the device is
#;           encrypted by 3rd party software, Insyde Hdd Password feature will not
#;           be supported.
#; SolutionDependency: IB15850116 fix the side effect caused by IB15850101 (adapted on 05.40.42)
#; Reviewer: IB06070000  
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Added:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\Override\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\Security\StorageSecurityCommandDxe\
#;   2. BilbyBoardPkg\Override\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\Security\StorageSecurityCommandDxe\Ia32\
#;   3. BilbyBoardPkg\Override\InsydeModulePkg\Universal\Security\StorageSecurityCommandDxe\Ia32\StorageSecurityCommandDxe.efi

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0014
#; Issue#: IB06070138
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: SATA
#; Symptom: On some projects that support IDE storage, when boot a IDE drive in Dual/Legacy
#;          boot mode, system would hang during POST.            
#; RootCause: After IB15850077, Atalegacy driver would assume all SATA relatd Bus driver (such as
#;            AhciBusdxe) would provide PCI configuration addresses in its devicepath, however,
#;            IDEBusdxe did not implement it. 
#; Description:1.(Bug Fix).
#;             2.(This version of Seamless SATA will labeled as 02.10.01.1229.00)
#;                AhciBusDxe  : 02.09.49.1203.00
#;                IdeBusDxe  : 02.09.25.0619.00
#;                AhciBusPei  : 02.09.43.1022.00
#;                IdeBusPei   : 02.04.01.1228.00
#;                AtaLegacySmm: 02.10.01.1229.00
#;                StorageSecurityCommandDxe: 02.09.43.1026.00                
#; Solution: Implement code to get PCI configuration addresses from device path that is 
#;           independant from Bus driver.  
#; SolutionDependency: This solution fix the side effect of IB15850077 (adopted on tag 05.32.25)
#; Reviewer: IB02960000

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0011
#; Issue#: IB02961278
#; Severity: Serious
#; Category: Security
#; Symptom: (Security)
#; RootCause: (Security)
#; Description: Add updated dbx files to FactoryCopyInfo folder to fix GRUB2 security hole. Build these updated dbx files to dbx database will cause old version Linux cannot boot in secure boot enabled environment. Kernel default behavior only adds these dbx files but not build them to BIOS. 
#; Solution: (Security)
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB06040000
#; RelatedFiles:
#; Added:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\FactoryCopyInfo\dbxupdate_amd64.auth
#;   2. BilbyBoardPkg\FactoryCopyInfo\dbxupdate_arm64.auth
#;   3. BilbyBoardPkg\FactoryCopyInfo\dbxupdate_x86.auth
#; Modified:
#;   1. BilbyBoardPkg\BIOS\BILBY.fd
#;   2. BilbyBoardPkg\FactoryCopyInfo\FactoryDefaultConfig.ini
#; 
#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0011
#; Issue#: IB06070098
#; Severity: Feature
#; Category: AGESA
#; Symptom: None
#; RootCause: None
#; Description: Update PI 1.2.0.5 RC1

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0009
#; Issue#: IB06070087
#; Severity: Medium
#; Category: Security Threat Reports
#; Symptom: (ITS63637) There are some security threats that current NVME legacy (CVE-2020-5952)
#;          driver did not handle which would lead to system failure.             
#; RootCause: 1. Hacker might randomly send SMI with incorrect commands, which
#;               might cause NVME R/W fail and cause system hang.
#;            2. Hacker might randomly send SMI with correct commands but include
#;               a buffer that located in SMMRAM or >1m.  This would destroy SMMRAM and 
#;               cause system hang.    
#; Description:1.(Bug Fix).
#;             2.(This version of NVMe will labeled as 01.05.11.0311.00)
#;                 NvmExpressDxe:       01.05.06.0206
#;                 NvmExpressPei:       01.04.25.0618
#;                 NvmExpressLegacySmm: 01.05.11.0311               
#; Solution: This solution is from Kernel 05.34.11 (IB15850189).
#;           1. The SMI handler directly returns if it is called with an unsupported operation specified by the CPU registers.
#;           2. The SMI handler directly returns if the buffer and length of the read/write specified by the CPU registers is an address > 1MB.
#;           3. Provide a tool for the vulnerability scanning. (See http://svn.insydesw.com/H2O-Kernel/Components/TestTool/Trunk/SmmVulTestTool)
#; SolutionDependency: None
#; Reviewer: IB06070000
#; RelatedFiles:

#; Issue#: IB06070086
#; Severity: Serious
#; Category: Security Threat Reports
#; Symptom: (ITS:0063636) Arbitrary code execution in SMM in SdLegacySmm (CVE-2020-5956).

#; Tag#: 05.32.50.0008
#; Issue#: IB06070080
#; Severity: Serious
#; Category: USB
#; Symptom: BIOS will hang on POST 0x1A when legacy boot
#; RootCause: USB SMI(hot plug) triggered between legacy boot event to first read KBC status command(in CSM)
#; Description: A freed instance(DXE UsbCore) being referenced by USB legacy control SMI handler(triggered by reading KBC status command) and cause system hang
